# Design system core

Read `AGENTS.md` and Storybook guides (`DesignPrinciples.mdx`, `Governance.mdx`) before editing.

## Architecture

- One package per **layer** (css, core, react, elements) — never a package per component
- CSS is the visual source of truth; React and Elements are thin wrappers with identical BEM output
- Shared logic lives in `@rgrmdesign/rgrm-ds-core` — never duplicate class-name builders

## Build order

CSS → Core → React + Elements → 3 sandboxes → Storybook (Overview + CSS + React + Web Components docs)

## Naming

- BEM: `.rgrm-{block}`, `.rgrm-{block}--{modifier}`, `.rgrm-{block}__{element}`
- Tokens: `--rgrm-{group}-{name}` (semantic, not primitive swatches)
- Web components: `<rgrm-{name}>` with `RGRM_{NAME}_TAG` constant

## Definition of done

A component is complete only when it exists in CSS, Core (`classNames` minimum), React, Elements, all three sandboxes, and Storybook with matching docs across all themes (Root / Dark / Brand).

## Release

- `pnpm changeset` → **minor** for new components; commit `.changeset/*.md`
- Never publish to npm from an agent run
- Peer tokens: `@rgrmdesign/rgrm-ds-tokens` — minimum in `packages/css/package.json` `peerDependencies` (`>=…` = any newer version OK)

Reference: Button in all layers (`packages/*/src/button/`).
